x4freetext: First counter consisted of a piece of plastic
scintillator 25 mu-m thick and 2.25 mm in diam. held
on the beam axis by means of a Melinex foil 6 mu-m
thick. The second passing counter was a piece of
plastic scintillator 50 mu-m x 3.75 mm diam. mounted
on an aluminium foil 0.25 mg/cm placed just inside the
first scintillation aperture of the antiscattering
counter.
The difference in the anticoincidence ratios for the
target in and target out runs was combined with the
difference due to the energy change in the defining
counters to give a "raw" experimental cross section.
Corrections were applied to "raw" cross section for
(1) energy unbalance between target and dummy, where
applicable,
(2) elastic scattering outside the stopping and
antiscattering counters
(3) inelastic scattering into the counters above the
bias levels.
